                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#1r #8v #16v #25r #36r #44r #50r #60r #71v #80r #86r #100r #113r #116r #122v #130r #144r #154r" facs="031 039 047 055 066 074 080 090 102 110 116 130 143 146 153 160 174 184">fols. 1r, 8v, 16v, 25r, 36r, 44r, 50r, 60r, 71v, 80r, 86r, 100r, 113r, 116r, 122v, 130r, 144r, 154r</locus> (colorful, elaborate <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign>);
                      <locus target="#16r #24v #35v #99v #115v #129r #153v" facs="046 055 066 130 146 159 184">16r, 24v, 35v, 99v, 115v, 129r, 153v, </locus> (multiple full stops with lines of red and black dots above and below);
                      <locus target="#43v #59v #71r #75r #79v #85v #113v #143v" facs="074 090 101 105 110 106 144 174">43v, 59v, 71r, 75r, 79v, 85v, 113v, 143v, </locus> (line of red and black dots);
                      <locus target="#167r #173r" facs="197 203">167r, 173r</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc>
                          Layman’s Prayer, in Amharic, <foreign xml:lang="am">አዳምን፡</foreign>, or <foreign xml:lang="am">ኖኅን፡</foreign> with incipit
                          <foreign xml:lang="am">
                            ኦ፡ እግዚእየ፡ ወአምላኪየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ አዳምን፡ ከሲኦል፡ ያወጻሕ፡ እኔንም፡ ከሲኦል፡ አስጻኝ።<gap reason="omitted"/>
                          </foreign>
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#xxvr(ecto)" facs="025"> f. xxvr(ecto), top</locus>: on the meaning of Maccabees, <foreign xml:lang="am">መቃብያን፡ ማለት፡ ዓቃብያነ፡ ሕገ፡ ኦሪት፡ ማለት፡ ነው። ፲፫ናቸው።</foreign>, “Maccabees means keepers of the Law and they are thirteen.”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#xxvr(ecto)" facs="025">f. xxvr(ecto), middle</locus>: Saying: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ነቀዙ፡ ለነዋይ፡ ብእሲት፡ ወውሉድ፡ እሙንቱ።</foreign>, “The weevil of wealth is wife and children.”</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#xxvr(ecto)" facs="025"> f. xxvr(ecto), in purple ink</locus>: note of birthday</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#66r" facs="099">Fol. 66r</locus> a small cross in the margin marks the midpoint of the psalms</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#177r" facs="207"> f. 177r, col. 2, in purple ink</locus>: Concluding prayer for Psalter</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                          Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#xiiir(ecto) #18r #19r #20r #50v" facs="013 048 049 050 081">folss. xiiir(ecto), 18r, 19r, 20r, 50v, </locus>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#64v #68v" facs="095 099">64v, 68v, </locus>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#xiiiv(erso) #118v #138r #151" facs="014 149 168 181">xiiiv(erso), 118v, 138r, 151, </locus>, etc.);
                          text has been removed (<locus target="#54r #63r #63v" facs="084 093 094">54r, 63r, 63v</locus>, etc.)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long,
                          the scribe completes the line of text above the end of the line (throughout). This scribe also will reduce the font size at the end of
                          lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#6r #10v #27r #28r" facs="036 041 057 058">fols. 6r, 10v, 27r, 28r</locus>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #xxivr(ecto) #xxivv(erso)" facs="001 002 024 025">Folss. ir(ecto), iv(erso), xxivr(ecto), xxivv(erso), </locus>, <locus from="xxviv(erso)" to="xxixr(ecto)" facs="027">xxviv(erso)–xxixr(ecto), </locus>, <locus target="#129v #173v #174r #174v #175r #175v #176r #176v #177v" facs="160 204 205 206 207 208">129v, 173v, 174r, 174v, 175r, 175v, 176r, 176v, 177v</locus> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
